law.text:
To value or classify property or to determine if a value or classification of property is correct, the Department may:
issue a subpoena:
for any person; or
for any evidence necessary to value or classify property or to determine if a value or classification is correct;
administer oaths and affirmations;
take depositions or other testimony;
issue written interrogatories with a notice of assessment;
if a person fails to comply with a subpoena, petition a circuit court to order compliance with the subpoena; or
if a person fails to file the annual report required under § 11-101 of this article, petition a court to compel the filing of the report.
